nodes.title: Fixed an issue when switching hackmodes, improved ice physics for adv hacks
Made ice slippery and added player animations when moving too fast on ice. Finished implementing terrain part of EnvSetAppearance
Added a workaround to the linux "TAB" issue
Added new adv option: Disable hacks
Fixed skins not rendering using ambient light
The water around the edge of the map, and bedrock is now rendered under custom ambient light
Implemented an experimental toggle to third-person mode (Pressing F6)
Selectionbox boundary lines are now drawn by the ShapeRenderer
Rewrote ShapeRenderer.java to allow the user to try and render using VBOs (Subject to GL Capabilities)
Changed packets to use int and not byte
Fixed HackState, readded Q and E
Added ability to change texturepacks in game by pressing esc. Added ability to save levels as .dat files
Added the ability to change the player's model to a block. New ChangeEntity specs: Send a blockID as a string that can be parsed to int if you want to change to a block
Added command-line args to allow launch of standalone versions. Added args: Server = args[0] Port = args[1] Player = args[2] Mppass = args[3]
Revert back some of the mouse code
Impl packets SetBlockPermissions, ChangeModel. Changing model testable code, new models "printer, chicken, croc"
Fixed mouse not grabbing correctly after chatinputscreen in new grabsmouse code
Per results from vote I secretly took (1 vote for yes, 0 votes for no) "Jonty800" now spawns as a sheep
Rewrite of way the mouse is grabbed and ungrabbed. Add MouseHelper.java
Only check if the display is active after the display has been updated
Formatted the entire source so future pushes are easier to read
Cleaned up 351 warnings over the entire source
Attempted mouse fixes. Stop lwjgl from downloading if its an applet
Fixed a potential glitch in playerList, playerList groups are now sorted by alphabetical order. changed lwjgl to unreal engine
Revert player physics & player list & packet work
Fixed player physics being really choppy
Selection boxs are now rendered through a buffer
Particles and mobs are now rendered correctly under custom lighting
Finished adding 15 new blocks, GuiNotificationScreen, ErrorScreen restar...
New packet to update allowed blocks, new block (50)
Improve font rendering, fix skin downloading thread
Fixed loading screens not working in applet
Rewrite of BlockSelectScreen.java to use all 49 blocks. Size changed to ...
Don't use ice physics when noclipping, fix +ophax
Fixed texture pack loading, singleplayer launching, and several other bugs.
Fixes in player skin/model and command-line arg handling.
EnvMapAppearance fix, third person mode no longer limited by -noClip, textures now freed properly.
Reduced memory pressure. Fixed #263. Added adaptive vsync.
Fixed "Reconnect" button not resetting the netcode properly. Fixes #294
Re-organized netcode, fixed refresh rate limit.
Cleanup / deobfuscation in Player and related classes.
Reworked chunk update limiting and fog.
Cleanup and commenting in TextureManager, Renderer, LevelRenderer, and BlockMap.
Created a new extension "CustomWorld" and reverted the fast leaves option
Bug fix, CPE Messagetype support (now to spec!)
Added a new graphics option 'fast leaves'
Fixed water rendering, did tons of other refactoring.
Refactoring, commenting, and cleanup in netcode.
Fixed ClassicWorld format compliance in LevelSerialzier
Simplified timing code (remove adjustment based on currentTimeMillis)
Client now logs GPU vendor, renderer info, and supported OpenGL version
Avoided rendering chunks in render pass 2 twice.
Minor cleanup in Renderer, ParticleManager, and MinecraftApplet
Fixed an issue with texture animations
Fixed a number of issues in TextureSelectionScreen
Fixed #241 Screenshots in singleplayer are saved to folder named "Generating level"
Removed FBO and OpenGlHelper (unused), renamed Frustrum to Frustum and some minor cleanup
Upgraded LWJGL to 2.9.1 and JInput to 2.0.5.
More cleanups, CustomAABB is now under minecraft.physics
Fixed the way standalone client shuts down. Now single-player levels actually get saved, every time.
Fixed problems with block model rendering.
Moved *intersect to its own helper, deobfuscated stuff, aligned some names to forge APIs
Removing dead code, fixing resource leaks, and expanding use of Java7 syntax.
Fixed settings not being loaded properly (embarrassingly easy fix).
Replaced all .0F instances with F (saves bytes!)
Fix for when clipboard is empty.
Code cleanup, moved Vec3D and Vertex to utils, renamed IOUtil to StreamingUtil
Fixed a couple residual issues in onMouseClick (thanks _123DMWM).
Code quality improvement batch #4 (split up run(), named OpenGL constants, fixed onMouseClick regression)
Code quality improvement batch #3 (resource download fix, leak fix, onMouseClick documentation)
Code quality improvement batch #2 (Minecraft$OS refactor, dead code removal)
Code quality improvement batch #1 (import cleanup, missing braces, for-loops)
Unify indentation to use spaces only
Fixed a possible NullPointerException and a bug in colour parsing.
Level refreshing when changing water level in options/
Fixed level size when loading/saving maps.
Added control options for more keys
FontRenderer.stripColor is now more efficient (notch y u do dis)
Added some Java Docs, cleanup, and some variable renaming.
Added icons to the custom textures.
Fix: some models caused the client crash.
Added new advanced option: "Show Names: Hover|Always". Stopped mojang emails from throwing 403's in the SkinDownloadThread
